# Cloudflare Pages _headers — served from the deploy root (staged from apps/website/).
#
# Purpose: keep the /legal/* accountability + governance documents out of search
# results. The raw `.md` docs cannot carry a `<meta name="robots">` tag (they are
# not HTML), so the X-Robots-Tag HTTP header is the only lever for them. The portal
# index.html also carries a noindex <meta>; this header makes the policy uniform.
#
# This does NOT block the telemetry release-gate, which fetches these URLs
# server-side (X-Robots-Tag only instructs crawlers, not fetchers).
#
# Security headers (CSP / HSTS / X-Frame-Options / etc.) are applied by the bound
# Cloudflare Worker (cloudflare/worker.js), NOT this file. The comprehensive
# security `_headers` template still lives at cloudflare/_headers (excluded from
# deploy by design); this root file intentionally carries only the /legal/* rule.

/legal/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex
